.SS "void write_log_with_tag (\fBlog_level_t\fP level, const char * tag, const char * title, const char * content,  \&.\&.\&.)"

.PP
Print the log tag, title and content to stdout/stderr\&. This function outputs the log tag, title and message with the approate header\&. e\&.g\&. [INFO] Main - Greetings: Hello\&.

.PP
In the example above, "Main" is the tag, "Greetings" is the title and "Hello\&." is the message body\&.

.PP
